GROUPING PATTERN
Threads T0-T3 and T16-T19 participate in MMA computation 1 (same A fragment data, rows 0-7)
Threads T4-T7 and T20-T23 participate in MMA computation 2 (same A fragment data, rows 0-7)
Threads T8-T11 and T24-T27 participate in MMA computation 3 (same A fragment data, rows 0-7)
Threads T12-T15 and T28-T31 participate in MMA computation 4 (same A fragment data, rows 0-7)

Within each computation group, threads T(n) and T(n+16) hold the same logical fragment elements {a0,a1,a2,a3} but correspond to different rows of the 8-row matrix A (rows 0-3 for the lower-numbered threads, rows 4-7 for the higher-numbered threads).

REGISTER PACKING DETAIL
Since the data type is .f16 (16-bit), two .f16 values are packed into each 32-bit register.
a0 and a1 are packed into one 32-bit register (a0 in bits 0-15, a1 in bits 16-31).
a2 and a3 are packed into a second 32-bit register (a2 in bits 0-15, a3 in bits 16-31).
Therefore each thread holds 2 physical 32-bit registers to store the 4 .f16 elements of the A fragment.

